They say a good night's sleep is the key to success - and Manchester United will certainly be hoping that proves the case on Sunday.

Louis van Gaal's and his players arrived at the Lowry Hotel in Manchester on Saturday evening ahead of their clash with QPR on Sunday.

New signings Radamel Falcao, Daley Blind and Marcos Rojo were all present, as were captain Wayne Rooney and Robin van Persie.

